    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Methacryloyloxy Hydroxypropyl Maltodextrin/Acrylates Crosspolymer is made by a two-step process. First, Maltodextrin is modified by reacting it with Glycidyl Methacrylate. The modified maltodextrin is then polymerized with a mixture of Acrylic Acid, Methacrylic Acid or one of their simple esters, and a crosslinker, Trimethylolpropane Triacrylate."
    ],
